1
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:18,518
My interview is tomorrow, why did I have to spill coffee?

2
00:00:18,518 --> 00:00:19,561
Just my luck.

3
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:21,312
Seriously.

4
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:27,652
That man is here again.

5
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:31,656
Unlike me, who gets beaten up on the battlefield every day,

6
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:34,075
this man always looks peaceful,

7
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:35,910
enjoying his vacation here.

8
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,996
He must have a damn lucky life.

9
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:48,131
Is someone here at dawn too?

10
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:04,314
Is he just here to rest?

11
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:18,953
What does he do for a living?

12
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:26,461
Hello.

13
00:01:26,461 --> 00:01:28,630
I am the applicant, Han Jaemin.

14
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:31,132
My strength is perseverance.

15
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:34,886
No, that's not it.

16
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:38,098
Everyone says perseverance.

17
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,141
Obsessiveness?

18
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:43,520
What if they see it as a weakness?

19
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:47,982
Prudence.

20
00:01:47,982 --> 00:01:51,069
I'd better go with prudence.

21
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:55,573
Wait.

22
00:01:56,866 --> 00:01:57,367
Huh?

23
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:00,036
That was close.

24
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:01,663
Close?

25
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:04,582
Your phone.

26
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:06,918
Did you want to buy a new one?

27
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,718
Sorry if I interrupted you.

28
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,762
I didn't put it in on purpose.

29
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,185
Thank you.

30
00:02:26,062 --> 00:02:28,439
I almost missed the interview results too.

31
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:30,608
Pardon?

32
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,027
Perseverance?

33
00:02:33,027 --> 00:02:34,737
Obsessiveness?

34
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:35,572
No.

35
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,198
Prudence?

36
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:39,033
You said that was your strength.

37
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:41,619
I thought you were listening to music.

38
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,748
I haven't finished my book yet,

39
00:02:45,748 --> 00:02:47,667
mind if I wait for the laundry next to you?

40
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:58,511
Thank you.

41
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,763
I should have bought this for you.

42
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:03,600
I just bought an extra one while getting mine. No big deal.

43
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,437
I'll enjoy it.

44
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:24,329
I guess I need to practice the interview again.

45
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:26,581
My weakness is clumsiness,

46
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:27,498
and my strength is...

47
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:30,585
Having a loud voice?

48
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:34,172
Are you teasing me right now?

49
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:36,966
Didn't you say that for me to hear?

50
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:38,301
You were peeking at me

51
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:40,345
and muttering since you walked in.

52
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:42,430
I wasn't peeking.

53
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:46,768
I just looked because I was envious.

54
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:52,523
Unlike me, struggling every day with interviews,

55
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,027
you looked so relaxed.

56
00:03:56,027 --> 00:03:57,195
I envied that.

57
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:01,282
You envy me?

58
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:06,204
I think I used to live similarly.

59
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:11,709
I struggled at a company for 10 years before quitting.

60
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:18,258
If I look relaxed now, I must have succeeded.

61
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:22,220
You quit a company you worked at for 10 years?

62
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,513
Yes.

63
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,725
While you were struggling to get in,

64
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:31,145
I must have been struggling to get out.

65
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:32,605
It's quite ironic.

66
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:33,731
Us.

67
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:37,068
He chose to be a bound spirit.

68
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:42,115
He was hiding a shadow behind that relaxed face.

69
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:45,326
Maybe this man and I come here

70
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:49,414
not to wash laundry, but to rinse our minds.

71
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:56,254
It seems done. I can go now, right?

72
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:01,301
Wait a moment!

73
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:08,099
I want to repay you.

74
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:09,976
You saved my phone

75
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:12,729
and bought me coffee.

76
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:29,746
Always keep your shirt collar stiff and upright.

77
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:34,459
Think of it as your self-esteem that won't crumble in any situation,

78
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:38,379
and carry it in your collar.

79
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:40,423
Then you'll have good results.

80
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,300
You look like a lucky person.

81
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,052
Me?

82
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:45,762
Yes.

83
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:49,140
You saved your phone,

84
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,266
and you met me.

85
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,988
Save the number.

86
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:05,406
"Laundry"

87
00:06:06,991 --> 00:06:08,951
Wanna make a bet?

88
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:11,371
If you pass, you buy the drinks.

89
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:12,914
If you fail, I'll buy.

90
00:06:13,414 --> 00:06:15,458
I buy the drinks?

91
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,251
Don't want to?

92
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:17,835
If not...

93
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:18,920
No.

94
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:20,546
I'd love to.

95
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:23,508
Make sure you pass.

96
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:25,051
If you don't want a free drink from me.

97
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:26,928
Okay.

98
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:32,392
Finally spoke to him.

99
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:35,478
But is this okay?

100
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:39,399
I don't have much time left here anyway.

101
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,292
(Text: Application Rejected)

102
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:00,503
Rejected again.

103
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:03,214
Why...

104
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:07,593
Why did I fail!

105
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:14,016
Mr. Laundry.

106
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:17,687
You said I would pass.

107
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:21,732
You said I was lucky.

108
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:23,943
But I failed...

109
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:38,499
Mr. Laundry...

110
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:42,587
I failed.
